<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-20 17:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UAE President Receives Phone Call From Saudi Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 20 (Xinhua) -- President of the United Arab
Emirates (UAE) Sheikh Zayed Bin Sultan Al-Nahyan Sunday received
a phone call from the crown prince of Saudi Arabia following the
defusing of a row between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In the phone call, Saudi Crown Prince Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz,
who is also deputy prime minister, reviewed with Zayed the results
of the meeting held Saturday between Saudi King Fahd Ibn Abdul-
Aziz and Qatari Emir Sheikh Hamad Bin Khalifa al-Thani, the
official WAM news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was aimed at clearing the atmosphere between the
UAE and Saudi Arabia on a unified stand on issues related to the
general interest of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC), the
agency said.
</P>
<P>
UAE newspapers said Sunday that the relations between the UAE
and Saudi Arabia had returned to normalcy following the Qatari
emir's mediation efforts to defuse their quarrel over improving
ties with Iran.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia's recent rapprochement with Iran irritated the
UAE, who has always required GCC members, including Saudi Arabia,
the UAE, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar and Bahrain, to help solve its
dispute with Iran first before improving ties with the country.
</P>
<P>
The UAE and Iran both claim the three islands of Abu Musa and
Greater and Lesser Tunbs, which are located near strategic
shipping lanes in the Gulf.
</P>
<P>
The islands have been occupied by Iran since 1971 when Britain
retreated from the region.
</P>
<P>
In the phone call, Crown Prince Abdullah expressed King Fahd's
great respect for the UAE president who reiterated his
appreciation for Saudi Arabia's support for the UAE, WAM said.
</P>
<P>
The UAE president also expressed his commitment to the "warm
and cordial relations" between the two countries and to uphold
the cooperation to achieve the joint objectives of both peoples.
</P>
</TEXT>
