<HEADLINE> AL Praises Qatar's Mediation Between Saudi Arabia, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Arab League (AL) on Sunday praised
Qatar's efforts to help clear up a misunderstanding between Saudi
Arabia and the United Arab Emirates (UAE).
</P>
<P>
AL Secretary General Esmat Abdel-Meguid said in a statement
that the efforts exerted by Qatari Emir Sheikh Hamad Bin Khalifa
al-Thani underline the keenness of the Arab Gulf states to
maintain strong ties.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid said the efforts "were crowned with success,"
commending the endeavors of Sheikh Hamad to remove inter-Arab
misunderstandings and clear up Arab atmospheres.
</P>
<P>
The warming-up of relations between Gulf countries, including
Saudi Arabia and Qatar, and Iran has aroused dissatisfaction and
suspicion of the UAE, which has disputes with Iran over three Gulf
islands - the Greater Tunb, the Lesser Tunb and Abu Musa.
</P>
<P>
Following a visit to Saudi Arabia and Qatar by Iranian
President Mohammad Khatami early this month, the UAE said the
rapprochement between the two Arab countries and Iran would
jeopardize its interests.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Hamad paid a short visit to the UAE on Saturday, after
which he, accompanied by UAE Minister of State for Foreign Affairs
Sheikh Hamdan Bin Zayed al-Nahyan, traveled to Saudi Arabia and
held talks with Saudi King Fahd and Crown Prince Abdullah in a bid
to dispel UAE's suspicion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
