<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Opposition Vows Not to Coop with Govt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the event of the government-appointed commission's draft
constitution being put to a referendum, Ncube said the NCA would
campaign for its rejection.
</P>
<P>
He said it would be impossible to come up with a new
constitution before next year's elections.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the people's convention had resolved that
political parties organize an all-party conference to agree on
minimal constitutional and electoral reforms to be made in order
to create an even playing field for the conduct of the elections.
