<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Youths to Attend Hawaii Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
HARARE, June 20 (xinhua) -- The Peace Child Zimbabwe, a non-
governmental organization that caters for the youth, will send 30
people in October to the Millennium Young People's Congress in
Hawaii.
</P>
<P>
 Peace Child Zimbabwe National Coordinator Leornard kachingwe
told the Zimbabwe News Agency Sunday that the congress would
discuss priorities for the youth in the next millennium.
</P>
<P>
"The congress will be the platform for the youth to tell the
world what they want to happen in the next millennium," he said.
</P>
<P>
The congress, funded by the United Nations, would be a
follow-up to the Rio Earth Summit Agenda 21 where world leaders
agreed to prioritize issues affecting the youth.
</P>
<P>
"We are saying the year 2000 is around the corner and the
youth must enter the millennium with a clear vision for the world
because they are the future of the world," Kachingwe said.
</P>
<P>
He said the congress would give Zimbabwean youths an insight
into other youths' vision for the millennium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
