<HEADLINE> Malaysian Party Ready to Face Election: Mahathir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad said here Sunday that the Barisan Nasional (BN)
is now more than ready to face the general election even if the
14-party coalition has to face opposition candidates on a
one-to-one basis.
</P>
<P>
"One-to-two or one-to-three doesn't matter to us. We will take
on everybody," the prime minister said when asked if the BN was
prepared to take on the opposition on a one-to-one basis in the
coming general election.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news conference at the end of the four-day 53rd
general assembly of the United Malays National Organization (UMNO)
 here, Mahathir who is also UMNO president, said the party would
now move forward and prepare for the general election.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether UMNO was stronger and united in facing the
general election, Mahathir said that based on the party's just
concluded general assembly, the members were now more spirited and
determined to defend and champion the party.
</P>
<P>
"They appeared very solid in responding to my opening speech
and at the closing of the assembly," he said.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 UMNO delegates attended the assembly, the last
for this century and also before the general election.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether the general election would be postponed until a
sodomy case against former Deputy Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim is
over, the prime minister said the government could not do this.
</P>
<P>
This is because a general election would have to be called once
every five years, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
