<HEADLINE> 3 Civilians Wounded in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Three Lebanese civilians were
injured on Sunday in an Israeli bombardment on villages in south
Lebanon, the Voice of the People radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The three Lebanese, including a five-year-old girl, were
wounded when an Israeli rocket hit a Lebanese civilian's house at
Gaobrih in the central sector of the Israeli occupied border zone
in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli attack came apparently as a response to previous
military operations launched by guerrillas of the Iranian-backed
Hezbollah, or Party of God, on its positions inside the zone.
</P>
<P>
The radio quoted security sources as saying that the Israeli
authorities have called on its residents in the northern area to
go into underground shelters as a precautionary measures against
possible retaliation by Hezbollah.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah usually fires Katyusha rockets into northern Israel
as a retaliation for the Israeli attacks which have killed
or wounded Lebanese civilians.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon
in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from
Lebanese guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting to dislodge Israeli occupation forces
and its ally South Lebanon Army out of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
