<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Anti-aircraft guns have been
placed at all airports in Pakistan, including the Islamabad
International Airport, officials of the Civil Aviation Authority
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Anti-aircraft guns have been placed at all the airports to
fight against any possible attack of India, the officials said,
adding that the armed forces have also taken various other steps
for the security of all the airports, especially the Islamabad
International Airport.
</P>
<P>
