NPC, CPPCC Chairmen Meet Norodom Ranarith Separately
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of China's National People's Congress
Standing Committee, and Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, met here today with Cambodian National Assembly
President Norodom Ranarith on separate occasions.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng noted China is happy to see that, following the
formation of the new National Assembly and government, the two
major parties of Cambodia, out of concern for the overall
interests of the country and the nation, have engaged in
cooperation, and made new progress in both domestic and foreign
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan stressed the third generation of the Chinese
leadership, with President Jiang Zemin at the core, will continue
to promote the friendly cooperation between the two countries,
proceeding from the existing solid basis.
</P>
<P>
DPRK-ROK Talks Postponed
</P>
<P>
The vice-ministerial talks between the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) and the Republic of Korea (ROK), which
were scheduled to be held in Beijing today, have been postponed.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have not reached agreement on when to hold the
talks.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that the talks were postponed because of the two
sides' differences on the fertilizer aid issue.
</P>
<P>
 Pakistan PM to Visit China
</P>
<P>
Nawaz Sharif, prime minister of Pakistan, will pay a working
visit to China as of June 28 at the invitation of Chinese Premier
Zhu Rongji, Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue announced
here today. 
