Relations between Russia and the NATO Western allies were badly
strained during the conflict in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Russia opposed NATO's airstrike campaign and later sent troops
into the provincial capital of Pristina ahead of NATO, a move that
surprised and exasperated the alliance. 
