<HEADLINE> Shanghai Aims to Become Asia-Pacific Economic Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 21 (Xinhua) -- This east China metropolis has
announced several measures to build itself into an economic center
for both the country and the Asian-Pacific area within a decade.
</P>
<P>
It will continue its endeavors to upgrade its industrial
development through fostering the information technology,
biopharmaceuticals, new materials and service industry sectors,
including financial and insurance services, said Mayor Xu Kuangdi.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at an investment forum here today, which
was sponsored by the British magazine ``The Economist."
</P>
<P>
"In order to play a greater role in the overall development of
China in the future, Shanghai should lay firm foundation for
building itself into a regional economic center," he said.
</P>
<P>
Stressing the importance of technological innovation, Xu said
that universities and research institutes will be closely
amalgamated with enterprises, so that new research findings can be
applied to industry more efficiently.
</P>
<P>
At the moment, Shanghai is carrying out a new round of
infrastructure construction, which includes a new international
airport in the Pudong New Area, a deep-water container port and a
project aimed at improving the local information network.
</P>
<P>
Xu also announced that transnational corporations will be
encouraged to open their regional headquarters in Shanghai,
promising that the procedures for approving foreign investment
projects will be further simplified. 
