<HEADLINE> Sampras Beats Draper to Advance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Top men's seed Pete Sampras of the
United States opened his Wimbledon defence on Monday by breezing
past Australian Scott Draper 6-3, 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, bidding for a sixth title here which would see him
overtake Swedish legend Bjorn Borg's Open era tally of five and
match the all-time men's Grand Slam haul of 12 by Australian Roy
Emerson, looked in superb form at home on the lush turf of the
Center Court.
</P>
<P>
Draper, the 1998 winner at Queen's Club where Sampras triumphed
10 days ago, could never find his rhythm and Sampras gained the
all-important break in the seventh game of the third set with a
stunning backhand service return winner.
</P>
<P>
The American then served out for the most routine of victories,
securing his win in a little under one and a half hours on his
first match point with a volley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
