<HEADLINE> Russian PM: All Ethnic Groups in Kosovo Must Be Protected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Sergei
Stepashin said here Monday that all ethnic groups in Kosovo must
be protected equally and the flow of Serb refugees from Kosovo
must be stopped.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the First World Congress of
the Russian Press, Stepashin said that Russian peacekeeping
efforts in the Yugoslav province would help stop the exodus of
Serb refugees.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement reached last week in Cologne, Germany, 3,
600 Russian troops will be stationed in several sectors in Kosovo
along with NATO troops.
</P>
<P>
Stepashin called for a rebuilding of trust between Serbs and
Kosovo Albanians, stressing that both ethnic Serbs and Albanians
must be protected.
</P>
<P>
"There should be no double standards on the settlement in
Kosovo," he said.
</P>
<P>
The First World Congress of the Russian Press has attracted
about 300 participants from 48 countries, and is scheduled to end
on Friday in the southern resort city of Sochi.
</P>
<P>
President Boris Yeltsin sent a greeting saying that the forum
will play a considerable role not only in strengthening contacts
between journalists, but also in uniting our compatriots from all
parts of the world.
</P>
<P>
Xinhua representatives is also taking part in the congress,
which is organized by the Itar-Tass news agency and the Russian
Press Institute. 
</P>
