<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK International Airport Important for HK Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Since it started operation a
year ago, the Hong Kong international airport has settled into a
routine of efficiency and is playing an important role in Hong
Kong's economic development and its continued prosperity.
</P>
<P>
In his first meeting with the media here Monday, Airport
Authority Chairman Victor Fung said that at the airport alone,
businesses are employing some 45,000 people and thousands more are
employed in downstream services such as hospitality, retailing and
other businesses.
</P>
<P>
Tourism income in 1998 amounted to 55.2 billion HK dollars, he
said, adding that total visitors for 1999 will reach 10 million
and total income will rise by 5.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Between its opening last July and the end of May this year, the
airport handled a total of 26.7 million arrivals and departures, 4.
8 percent more than the same period of the previous year, said
Fung, who took up his post earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
With the best facilities in the world, the airport now has an
average of 450 flights, 90,000 arrivals and departures and more
than 4,500 tons of cargo every day.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 60 airlines operating some 3,000 flights
between Hong Kong and 110 cities around the world. There are
direct flights from Hong Kong to nearly 40 inland cities and
demand for aviation services is growing, he said.
</P>
<P>
The latest surveys conducted by the airport show that more than
90 percent of the passengers are satisfied with the airport
services.
</P>
<P>
However, there's still room for improvement, he said, pledging
that the airport will do its best to enhance the overall services
to meet the increasing demand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
