<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Cambodian National Assembly President (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met here
today with Cambodian National Assembly President Norodom Ranarith.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that, under the leadership of King Norodom Sihanouk,
Cambodia has smoothly realized ethnic reconciliation. China is
happy to see that, following the formation of the new National
Assembly and government, the two major parties, out of concern for
the overall interests of the country and the nation, have engaged
in cooperation, and made new progress in both domestic and foreign
affairs, he added.
</P>
<P>
China highly appreciates King Sihanouk's unique and important
role in safeguarding national stability, realizing ethnic
reconciliation and speeding up economic growth, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the new Cambodian government mapped out its
political guiding principles based on the consensus between the
two parties, and this accords with the practical situation of the
country and the basic interests of its people.
</P>
<P>
China, as a close neighbor of Cambodia, sincerely hopes that
the Cambodian people, under the leadership of King Sihanouk, will
take an ethnically harmonious, politically stable and economically
developing Cambodia into the next century, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the NPC, Chinese government and people all harbor
great respect for King Sihanouk, highly value their good-
neighborly ties with Cambodia and respect the development course
chosen by the Cambodian people in accordance with their own
situation.
</P>
</TEXT>
