<HEADLINE> Shanghai Attracts More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investment has kept a
steady momentum in this east China metropolis, and is showing
signs of increasing. This is the result of special efforts made by
the Shanghai municipal government, said Zhu Xiaoming, head of the
Shanghai Municipal Foreign Trade and Economic Commission, here
today.
</P>
<P>
In the January-May period, Shanghai approved 585 overseas-
invested projects, up 28.3 percent compared with the same period
of last year. Overseas-invested enterprises exported 3.85 billion
U.S. dollars-worth of goods, up 34.96 percent, and the service
industry attracted 1.06 billion U.S. dollars in foreign investment,
accounting for 60.5 percent of the total foreign investment the
city attracted, up 35 percent compared to the same period of the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Investment from the United States and Hong Kong was up; about
95 U.S.-invested projects were set up in Shanghai in the first
five months of this year.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-invested enterprises tended to re-invest, Zhu noted,
and more overseas investors want to run their enterprises in
Shanghai themselves.
</P>
<P>
Zhu noted that Shanghai aims to attract four billion U.S.
dollars in overseas investment this year, channel overseas
investment to high-tech industry, and encourage overseas investors
to cooperate with private and non-state enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
