<HEADLINE> China Telecom to Put More Enterprises into Cyberspace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 21 (Xinhua) -- China Telecom is aiming to put
more enterprises into cyberspace. So far, the company has over two
million on-line customers, nearly 200 of which are enterprises.
</P>
<P>
A China Telecom official revealed this at a symposium on the
government on-line program here today.
</P>
<P>
Besides having established nationwide telephone and mobile
phone networks, China has also set up multi-media networks.
</P>
<P>
China Telecom will also find a way to put more families into
cyberspace, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The company established an on-line business certificate system
in August 1998, and has developed on-line securities, on-line
shopping and on-line medicare since last November.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that China Telecom aims to expand various kinds
of cooperation with enterprises, and will also provide services
like website design, information updating and technology training
for its customers.  
