<HEADLINE> HK Government to Finance 64 Industrial Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong government will
use its Industrial Support Fund to finance 64 projects approved by
the Industry and Technology Development Council (ITDC) this
financial year, according to ITDC Secretary Annie Choi.
</P>
<P>
The fund, established in 1994 and provided on a yearly basis,
aims to support projects that can contribute to Hong Kong's
industrial or technology development. A total of 374 projects have
been supported in the last five financial years.
</P>
<P>
The objectives of the successful projects this year could be
broadly categorized as infrastructure support, development of new
technologies or products, personnel training and promotional
activities such as industry or technology conferences.
</P>
<P>
Of the 64 approved applications, 50 have already secured
industrial sponsorship either in cash or in kind, Choi said.
</P>
<P>
The total project costs amount to some 282.3 million HK dollars
(about 36.19 million U.S. dollars), to be used over five years, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Of these successful applications, 33 are from higher education
institutions, 14 from industrial support bodies, 16 from trade and
industrial organizations and one from a research institute, Choi
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
