<HEADLINE> Iranian Leader Urges West to Correct Stances </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah
Ali Khamenei Monday reiterated Iran's adherence to Islamic
principles and urged the western countries to correct their
stance toward Iran.
</P>
<P>
Iran will never try to justify its Islamic stands and
principles in dealing with the west, it is the westerners that
must correct their wrong stances, he said.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting Speaker of Sudanese National
Assembly Hassan al Turabi, Khamenei said that in its relations
with other countries, Iran will consider mutual interests and
counter all arrogant tendencies.
</P>
<P>
He cited materialization of the Islamic rule and opposition to
arrogance as two features of Islamic sovereignty, the Islamic
Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The reason for all the hostilities of the global arrogance
toward Iran and Sudan is because the two states practice Islam, he
said, stressing that showing leniency and trying to draw the
temporary consent of the arrogant powers will not remove these
hostilities.
</P>
<P>
The arrogant powers will not be happy with anything less
than full dominance and this is something that the Islamic
Republic of Iran will never accept, he said.
</P>
<P>
Turabi is currently in Iran for a two-day founding conference
of the Parliamentary Union of the Organization of the Islamic
Conference, which ended on Thursday. 
</P>
