<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets Norodom Ranarith </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua)-- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), met with Norodom Ranarith, president of the
National Assembly of Cambodia, here today.
</P>
<P>
Li said China and Cambodia are close neighbors, and enjoy a
tradition of friendly relations. Since the establishment of the
People's Republic of China in 1949, friendship between the two
countries has progressed on a sustainable basis, withstanding the
test of time, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese people will never forget the strong support
extended to China by King Norodom Sihanouk and the Cambodian
government on many important issues, he added.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that the third generation of the Chinese leadership,
with President Jiang Zemin at the core, will continue to promote
the friendly cooperation between the two countries, proceeding
from the existing solid basis.
</P>
<P>
He said Cambodia boasts rich natural resources and a fine
climate, and the Cambodian people, after years of war, cherish
peace and stability all the more, and are especially longing for
development and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that, under the leadership of King
Sihanouk, Cambodia will successfully achieve its goals, including
reconstruction, developing its economy and improving its living
standards.
</P>
<P>
Ranarith said that the friendship between Cambodia and China
was established by the leaders of the older generation, and so, as
their successors, the present leadership generation is responsible
for continuing such friendship.
</P>
<P>
On his current trip, Ranarith said, he aims to reinforce
cooperation between the two countries as well as the two
parliaments; at the same time, he intends to examine the
tremendous achievements made by the Chinese people in reform and
opening up.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the Cambodian government, Ranarith thanked the
Chinese government for its consistent assistance, both political
and economic. He said that the domestic situation of Cambodia is
now turning toward stability, and the economic reconstruction work
has also returned to the normal track. He expressed the hope that
the two countries would further expand mutually-beneficial
cooperation in the economic and trade sector.
</P>
<P>
Ranarith is on a official goodwill visit at the invitation of
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of China's National
People's Congress.  
</P>
</TEXT>
