<HEADLINE> Hong Kong EFIL to Launch Unit Trust Product </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Exchange Fund
Investment Limited (EFIL) announced here Monday to launch a unit
trust product tracking the Hang Seng Index as a means of its
shares disposal program.
</P>
<P>
However, the EFIL declined to give the details and timing of
the launch, since more preparatory work is needed before the
details are finalized, said Ti-liang Yang, chairman of the EFIL,
in a press briefing after an EFIL Board meeting Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
Yang said the primary objective of the EFIL remains the
disposal of the shares in Hong Kong equity portfolio in an orderly
manner without disrupting the market.
</P>
<P>
"Having considered various methods of disposal, the Board has
concluded that it would be appropriate to launch the disposal
program in the form of a unit trust product tracking the Hang Seng
Index," he noted.
</P>
<P>
At this stage, the EFIL would recommend for an application to
be made for this unit trust product to be listed on the Stock
Exchange of Hong Kong, Yang said, adding that the minimum
denomination of the units would be of a size that would facilitate
participation by the retail public in the region.
</P>
<P>
Yang also outlined a number of advantages of the unit trust
approach in comparison to other disposal methods.
</P>
<P>
"It can cater for the needs of both retail and institutional
investors, but does not involve the selection of individual stocks
and is therefore 'market neutral,' while it offers the prospect of
the least disruption to the market," he said.
</P>
<P>
Yang revealed that at least four to five months is needed to
complete the preparatory work such as market research, government
approval and market promotion.
</P>
<P>
"Quite apart from getting ready in terms of documentation and
procedures, the decision to launch this unit product and the
timing of the launch will depend on the prevailing market
conditions," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
