<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Host Cyber Week for 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- A series of community-based
activities known as the Cyber Week '99 will soon be kicked off in
a bid to enhance public understanding of the use of information
technology.
</P>
<P>
The programs to be held here between June 24 and 30 include
seminars, roving exhibitions, Universal Free Electronic Mail
Service Scheme, E-community Ambassador, community Cyber Point and
a new Digital 21st century web page.
</P>
