<HEADLINE> Remains of Former Vice-Premier Cremated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The remains of Chen Xilian, a
former vice-premier of China, who died June 10 at the age of 85,
were cremated here today.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress, Vice-Premier Li Lanqing and other Chinese
leaders attended a mourning ceremony for Chen at Babaoshan
Revolutionary Cemetery.
</P>
<P>
Chen was a former member of the Standing Committee of the
Central Military Commission and a former member of the Political
Bureau of Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Chen joined the Chinese Red Army in 1929, and joined the CPC in
1930. He was granted the military rank of general in 1955, and
later became commander of China's artillery forces.
</P>
<P>
Chen also served as commander of the Shenyang and Beijing
military area commands. 
</P>
