<HEADLINE> Nigerian President to Visit S. Leone Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's President Olusegun
Obasanjo may pay a visit Friday to Sierra Leone to push for the
ongoing peace process in the strife-torn west Africa country,
said a Nigerian daily newspaper Monday.
</P>
<P>
This Day, a leading Nigerian daily, said the visit will be
Obasanjo's first to the country since he assumed power on May 29.
The president is expected to discuss bilateral issues as well as
the ongoing peace talks in Lome, Togo with his Sierra Leone
counterpart Tejan Kabbah.
</P>
