<HEADLINE> Ancient Architecture Exhibition Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- China's only museum of ancient
architecture today unveiled an exhibition of the country's
traditional architectural art, as part of the programs associated
with an upcoming international gathering of architects.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Museum of Ancient Architecture is presenting a
large number of relics, models, documents and pictures which
depict the technology, esthetics and history of Chinese
architecture.
</P>
<P>
The exhibits are divided into the categories of city, palace,
temple, dwelling, garden and mausoleum architecture.
</P>
<P>
The 20th World Congress of the International Union of
Architects, which will open here Wednesday, has put the exhibition
on its program, according to the Beijing Municipal Cultural
Heritage Administration, which is sponsoring the display.
</P>
<P>
Special items of the display include a miniature of the ancient
city of Beijing, a model of a 2,000-year-old courtyard, and wooden
models of some famous examples of Chinese architecture, such as
Beijing's Temple of Heaven.  
</P>
</TEXT>
