<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Journalist Arrested for Genocide in Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 21(Xinhua) -- Rwandan government claimed to have
arrested a woman journalist with the infamous Radio Television
Libre des Milles Collines (RTLM) which played a prominent role in
inciting Hutus to exterminate Tutsis during the 1994 genocide.
</P>
<P>
''Valerie Bemeriki was arrested in northwestern Rwanda late
last week and will be prosecuted for genocide and crimes against
humanity,'' Rwandan judicial officials announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
Bemeriki is most sadly recalled for her incitation to the
mass-killings of Tutsis and opposition Hutus in April - July 1994
on the infamous RTLM, the Rwandan News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Bemeriki is on the list of the more than 1,000 most-wanted
genocide criminals, made by the Rwandan government in 1996, who
are said to be planners, executioners, and ring-leaders of the
mass-killings.
</P>
<P>
The RTLM was created in mid-1993 as a private radio, but its
main share- holders were members of the family of President
Juvenal Habyarimana who wanted an instrument that could help
destroy the Arusha Peace Accord signed by the government and the
armed opposition of the Rwandan Patriotic Front. 
</P>
</TEXT>
