<HEADLINE> China's Largest Special Economic Zone Has Best Air, Seawater </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 21 (Xinhua) -- A recently released bulletin from
the island province of Hainan, China's biggest special economic
zone (SEZ), says that it has the best air and seawater in the
country, but it also admits that Hainan suffers from noise
pollution.
</P>
<P>
The bulletin says that the seawater in a majority of the island
's bays and estuaries meets China's highest quality standards and
that major tourist zones are pollution-free.
</P>
<P>
Its various air quality indexes meet the state's highest
environmental and atmospheric standards. In Haikou, the provincial
capital, the weekly air quality index is at the top of the quality
scale.
</P>
<P>
Local sources say that the province spent 1.54 million yuan on
air pollution controls in 1998 and shut down five industrial
polluters and forced 10,000 motor vehicles to switch to un-leaded
gasoline.
</P>
<P>
The province will also use various other means to increase
protection of the environment and to control pollution. It has a
plan to maintain natural resources and the environment as part of
a national economic spending system. 
</P>
