<HEADLINE> Kuwait Bans Imports of Belgian Meat, Foodstuffs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait Monday decided to ban
importing all types of Belgian meat, dairy products and
foodstuffs of animal origin.
</P>
<P>
The decision, which was announced by Minister of Commerce and
Industry Heshan Suleiman Al-Oteibi, also bans the import of
animal feed, the Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will take every necessary measure against all
violators, the decision said.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti Municipality early this month suspended the import
of Belgian poultry and eggs due to risks of the cancer-causing
dioxin contamination. 
</P>
