<HEADLINE> Renovation of Tian'anmen Square Near Completion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The eight month long renovation of
the Tian'anmen Square in downtown Beijing is nearing completion
and on Sunday gardeners, aided by People's Liberation Army
soldiers, began to lay turf on two newly constructed lawns.
</P>
<P>
"They each cover an area of 4,800 square meters and will bring
the total green space in the square area up to nearly 14,000
square meters," said an official in charge of the renovation
project.
</P>
<P>
The renovation of Tian'anmen Square, which is reputed to be the
world's largest city square, started at the end of last October as
part of the preparations for the celebration of the 50th founding
anniversary of the People's Republic of China on October 1 this
year.
</P>
<P>
Employees of the Beijing City Gardening Administration and more
than 400 soldiers and officers from the PLA Beijing Garrison
started laying turf at around 7 a.m. Sunday, and the work is
expected to be completed before June 25.
</P>
<P>
"After that, the renovation project will soon be concluded and
the square will reopen to domestic and foreign visitors," said the
official.
</P>
<P>
According to Hou Yinglun, an official with the engineering
department of the Beijing City Gardening Administration, the grass
planted on the square grows very fast and can withstand cold
weather. It can thus coat the square in a green sward for some 300
days a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
