<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panchen Lama Makes Pilgrimage to Resting Place of Predecessors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIGAZE, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The 11th Panchen Lama this morning
paid a pilgrimage to the soul towers of most of the late Panchen
lamas at the Zhaxi Lhumbo Lamasery, in Shigaze, the second largest
city in the Tibet Autonomous Region, southwest China.
</P>
<P>
During his pilgrimage, the 11th Panchen Lama, who is nine years
of age in earthly terms, swore to inherit and practice the will of
his predecessors and be a good living Buddha.
</P>
<P>
He started his pilgrimage in the Qamba Hall by making kowtows
and donating a hada (a white silk ribbon) to the statue of the
Qamba Buddha, the god of the future.
</P>
<P>
He then went to the hall housing the soul tower of the late
10th Panchen Lama, again practicing kowtows and making hada
donations while also reading sutras.
</P>
<P>
The 11th Panchen Lama also attended the hall accommodating the
soul tower of the 4th Panchen Lama and the hall that keeps the
soul towers of the 5th, 6th, 7th, 8th and 9th Panchen lamas.
</P>
<P>
According to Tibetan Buddhist theory, the Panchen lamas are a
reincarnation of their previous souls and, therefore, the 11th
Panchen Lama is the reincarnation of the 10th.
</P>
<P>
The 11th Panchen Lama made the pilgrimages to the soul towers
of former Panchen lamas in order to inherit their will and to
display the power of the Buddha.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion of the pilgrimage, he said, "All the former
Panchen lamas were patriotic and loved the religion."
</P>
<P>
The 11th Panchen Lama pledged that he must inherit the will of
the late Panchen lamas, follow the instructions by President Jiang
Zemin, whose inscription for the Zhaxi Lhumbo Lamasery reads, "
Safeguard the nation and benefit the people."
</P>
<P>
He will work hard to educate himself in the Buddhist doctrine,
be widely engaged in charitable activities and become a good
living Buddha who is patriotic and also loves the religion, he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
