<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Stresses Importance of Monitoring the Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Yellow River has been the
scene of frequent disasters over the past 2,500 years and dykes on
the lower reaches have been breached more than 1,500 times.
</P>
<P>
Now China's President Jiang Zemin has called for unremitting
efforts to control the floods of this mighty river, better use its
water resources and create a good ecological environment along its
length.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin made his remarks today in the capital of
central Henan Province and explained, "This has always been a
major task for the Chinese nation and is of great strategic
significance to the sustained socio-economic development along the
river and nationwide."
</P>
<P>
Jiang was addressing a forum on the topic attended by Vice-
Premier Wen Jiabao, leading officials from Henan and Shandong
provinces and high-ranking military officers.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the river has withstood floods since 1949,
when the People's Republic of China was founded, attributing that
success to the consistent efforts of the Chinese people in water
control under the correct leadership of the Communist Party of
China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang urged that further efforts be taken in exploring new ways
to control and develop the river from a long-term perspective.
</P>
<P>
"The general principle in this regard is to combine water
control, rational uses of water resources and the improvement of
the ecological environment together to seek a coordinated
development of the economy, population, resources and environment,
" he said.
</P>
<P>
He called for the strengthening of river dykes, the dredging
of the river course and prevention of soil from erosion by
applying modern technology to ensure the long-term safety of the
river.
</P>
<P>
Jiang asked local governments to be fully prepared for possible
flooding this year, stressing that one of the important
experiences learned in successfully combating last summer's
flooding of the Yangtze and Nenjiang rivers is the importance of
taking preventative measures.
</P>
<P>
He said that emergency personnel should be well-organized,
flood-fighting equipment stocked in advance and the army and local
people ready to increase their cooperation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
