<HEADLINE> Guangzhou No. 1 Metro to Open Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Guangzhou Subway Corporation
announced here today that the city's No. 1 Metro will become
official operational on June 28.
</P>
<P>
General Manager Lu Guangsen said the building of the 18.48 km-
long subway was started in December 1993 and has cost 12.72
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Part of the Metro began to operate on a trial basis on June 28,
1997 and during the Spring Festival earlier this year the whole
subway was put into experimental use for two weeks.
</P>
<P>
Recently, experts from Hong Kong, Beijing and Shanghai were
invited to study the safety and reliability of the new subway in
Guangzhou. They gave the greenlight to the official launch.
</P>
<P>
It is a 32 minute journey for subway passengers to travel from
the Xilang Station to the Guangzhou East Station and 300,000
passengers are expected to travel on it every day. 
</P>
