<HEADLINE> Macao Satellite Television Starts Formal Broadcast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Macao Satellite Television
Station started its formal broadcast Monday following a grand
inauguration ceremony participated by high-ranking local officials.
</P>
<P>
"We will exert great efforts to make people around the world
know more about Macao and about its unique feature mixing both
Chinese and western cultures over the past centuries," said Ng Fok,
chairman of the board of directors of the station.
</P>
<P>
Macao is under the rule of the Portuguese Macao government. On
December 20 this year, the Chinese government will resume the
exercise of sovereignty over Macao.
</P>
<P>
The television station launched its trial operation on May 18,
offering two hours of tourism program every day to the areas
including China's mainland, Hong Kong, Taiwan, Macao and some
Southeast Asian countries. The program is broadcast in Chinese
Mandarin, Cantonese and English.
</P>
<P>
Ng Fok said he was confident that the television would
establish its fame in the Asian-Pacific areas in the near future.
In the long run, TV programs from the station will be available in
more than 70 countries and territories around the world. 
</P>
