HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong went
down four HK dollars to close at 2,396 HK dollars a tael on Monday,
according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 259.26 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, 0.45 U.S. dollars down from the previous close at Monday's
exchange rate of one U.S. dollar against 7.7575 HK dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
