<DOCNO> XIE19990621.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close 4.37 Percent Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks soared 585.96
points, or 4.37 percent, to close at 13,994.23 Monday, setting a
record high since October in 1997.
</P>
<P>
This was believed to be buoyed by news of the government's plan
to list its large equity holdings in a unit trust and potential
impact of an interest rate hike in the United States as well as
backing efforts made by several of the Group of Seven leading
industrialized nations to push for the restart of the talks for
China's entry into the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
The biggest factor affecting the market was the positive result
in last week's government land tender, brokers said.
</P>
<P>
The market's turnover climbed to 12.094 billion HK dollars (1.
55 billion U.S. dollars), 3.691 billion HK dollars (473 million U.
S. dollars) more than that of last Thursday, the day before the
Dragon Boat Festival.
</P>
<P>
Shares for finance, utilities, properties and commerce and
industry registered strong gains of 3.34 percent, 5.98 percent, 6.
23 percent and 2.60 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares also increased sharply with the Hang Seng
China Enterprises Index going up 6.58 percent to 536.34 points and
the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index up 5.11 percent
to 1,123.72 points.
</P>
<P>
China Telecom led the market higher, soaring 2.35 HK dollars or
11.68 percent to 22 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
The stock market gained 149.71 points, or 1.1 percent, to 13,
557.98 after a few minutes opening.
</P>
<P>
The HSI rose 217,13 points, or 1.62 percent, to close the
morning session at 13,625.40. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
