<HEADLINE> New Exhibition Will Highlight Chinese Art </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Artists and photographers from
home and abroad are being invited to submit their works for a new
exhibition of such works.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the Ministry of Culture, the Chinese Artists'
Association and other related arts groups, the exhibition plans to
offer a wider creative space for artists worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Any traditional Chinese paintings worked out in recent years in
various themes, styles and forms are eligible and photographic
entries will be classified into such topics as economic
construction, daily life, social customs, natural beauty and art
in general.
</P>
<P>
The deadline for submissions is September 20 and a special
committee of leading artists will evaluate the works for future
exhibition.  
</P>
