<HEADLINE> Harbin Trade Fair Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The 10th China Harbin Economic and
Trade Talks came to an end today in this capital of Heilongjiang
Province, in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Contracts worth 3.57 billion U.S. dollars were signed at the
week-long fair, which attracted more than 50,000 participants from
over 50 countries and regions, including over 6,000 overseas
businessmen.
</P>
<P>
This year's fair was also a good opportunity for boosting
cooperation between domestic companies. During the fair, domestic
participants signed 9.94 billion yuan worth of contracts, more
than at any previous fair.
</P>
<P>
According to Heilongjiang's deputy governor, Wang Zhenchuan,
124 overseas companies and 1,023 domestic firms exhibited products
during the fair, at which 1,000 pavilions were available.
</P>
</TEXT>
