<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Score Another Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LOS ANGELES, June 20 (Xinhua) -- After beating China in a
close-door friendly days ago, Nigeria won a game which really
matters, beating DPR Korea 2-1 in a Group A match at the women's
World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Playing on the excellent turf of Rose Bowl, the Nigeria fully
displayed their technique and understanging of soccer, taking control
of the match for most of the time.
</P>
<P>
Yet they met a stiff defense from the DPR Korean team which is
better organized.
</P>
<P>
The two teams played to a goalless draw after the first half and
only 5 minutes into the second half, Mercy Akide broke down to the
right and released a fierce from close range. The DPR Korean
goal-keeper Kye Yong Sun tried hard but still failed to punch out the
shot.
</P>
<P>
The DPR Korean team levelled the score at 1-1 at the 73rd
miunute through Jo Song Ok who tapped in a Jo Jong Ran cross.
</P>
<P>
Only five minutes later, Rita Nwadike hit in the winner for
Nigeria when she completed a string of excellent passes with a
well-poised shot.
</P>
<P>
The win boosted Nigeria's hopes of qualifying for the second
round as they are now has the same points with group leaders the
United States, only ranked second as the United States had a better
goal difference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
