<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Companies Sign Telecom Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Two companies from Russia and China
have signed an agreement to jointly launch a project to upgrade
the outdated program-controlled telephone exchange system in
Sverdlovskaya Oblast, a state of Russia.
</P>
<P>
The two companies, the Import and Export Co. (Group) Ltd. of
Harbin, capital of northeast China's Heilongjiang Province which
borders on Russia, and the Ural Telecom Company of Sverdlovskaya
Oblast, will invest a total of 80 million U.S. dollars in the
project.
</P>
<P>
A source with the Harbin company noted that the company had
beaten several international telecom giants to win the deal. The
company will take charge of the design of the whole project, and
all telecom facilities required in the project will be supplied by
Chinese manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
The project will be carried out in three phases. The first
phase of the project, which is expected to cost some 13 million U.
S. dollars, is scheduled to be completed within three years,
according to the source.  
</P>
</TEXT>
