Central African President Ange-Felix Patasse attended the signing
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
-- The French state-owned consulting firm Systra has been
contracted as a technical advisor for the new subway planned for
Shenzhen city, China's first special economic zone in the south.
</P>
<P>
-- China's imports surged 15.3 percent in the first five months
of the year, the highest growth rate since May 1996, latest
statistics released by the General Administration of Customs show.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese enterprises have been invited to invest in
infrastructure construction projects in Bulgaria. The request came
from visiting Bulgarian Foreign Minister Nadezhda Mikhailova here
last Thursday who made the remarks at a Sino-Bulgarian commercial
seminar.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese trade minister and visiting Bahrain minister of
finance and national economy signed an agreement here last
Thursday to encourage mutual investment.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese trade minister Shi Guangsheng met with visiting
British Secretary of State for Trade and Industry Stephen Byers
here last Thursday, to exchange views on trade between China and
the United Kingdom, between China and the European Union and on
China's accession to the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
-- Leading automobile manufacturers the world over have rushed
to the ongoing six-day Shanghai International Automotive Industry
Show, which opened on June 15, with their newest models to tap the
potential of the huge Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
-- An express shipping service carrying fresh food between
China and Japan has recently been launched by the China Ocean
Shipping Company which has set up a new container company to
handle the route.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese export companies have been told to improve the
quality and standard when using wooden boxes for packing their
export products, according to a special notice issued by the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation and several
other ministerial departments.
</P>
<P>
-- China and Germany recently announced plans to carry out a
five-year cooperation project designed to reform and develop small
and medium-sized non-state-owned Chinese enterprises.  
