<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Roaring on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Share Prices surged up on
Singapore Stock Market Monday as the stronger-than-expected trade
growth for May spurred market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) shot up 49.75 points to
a new two-year high of 2,120.38 points, piercing the 2,100-point
level and less than 50 points away from its all-time high of 2,163
points about two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Total volume soared to 2,222.55 million shares worth 1,898.49
million Singapore dollars (1,111.72 million U.S. dollars). Gainers
outstripped losers by 342 to 22 with 79 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
ICT topped the volume list as it had 110.15 million shares
traded. It was followed by AFP which had 93.37 million units done.
Frt Links was the next with 90.71 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Venture was the biggest gainer of the day as it jumped up 180
cents to close at 15.30 Singapore dollars. YHS ran up 120 cents to
finish at 7.00 Singapore dollars. GE Life gained 110 cents to end
at 22.50 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On downside, SIA F and UOB F shed 10 cents to close at 15.80
and 11.70 Singapore dollars respectively. SingTel retreated eight
cents to finish at 3.04 Singapore dollars. Network w00, SingTel 10
and SingTel 100 dipped six cents each to end at 0.63, 3.02 and
3.02 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the release of the stronger-than-expected growth
of May external trade boosted the market.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Trade Development Board said in a press release
Monday that external trade expanded by 4.6 percent after 12
consecutive months of contraction with non-oil domestic exports
growing by 7.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Dealers also noted that the buying frenzy by retail investors
also helped push small-capital issues to the center stage.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
