<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Force Seeded Germany to a 1-1 Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LOS ANGELES, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Group B seeded team Germany played
unconvincingly in their first match at the third women's World Cup and
had to settle for a 1-1 draw with Italy here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Germany dominated the match, especially in thye first half as
they out-shot their Italian opponents 9-3.
</P>
<P>
Italy had just one shot on goal in the first half and that was
enough for them to take a 1-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
Assisted by Antonella Carta, Patrizia Panico beat the German
goal-keeper at the 36th minute to give Italy a surprising lead.
</P>
<P>
The German team played hard but their equalizer didn't come
until the 61st minute when they were awarded a penalty. Betina
Wegmann made no mistake from the spot.
</P>
<P>
Italian coach Carlo Facchin was happy with the result:"We are
satisfied with the one point. When we have more conviction of being
a team, that's when we will be a team."
</P>
<P>
Facchin's German counterpart Tina Theune-Meyer said:"We gave the
Italians too much space. Of course one point is not satisfying but
we were not putting it away."
</P>
<P>
Group B also includes Brazil and Mexico. Brazil now top the
group after trouncing Mexico 7-1 on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Only the top two teams from each of the four groups qualify for
the second round which adopts a knock-out systeam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
