<HEADLINE> Improving Facilities At China's Schools In The Northeast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Education departments in China's
Jilin Province are introducing the Internet service into local
schools.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the departments are improving education facilities
at schools. They have allocated 17.65 million yuan (2.1 million U.
S. dollars) for 679 slide projectors, 619 screens, 775 record
players, 274 color TVs, 95 video players, 2,324 computers, and
other facilities for primary and high schools in the city of
Changchun.
</P>
<P>
The developing information industry has inspired the city to
accelerate the use of modern technology for education to provide
students greater opportunities to get up-to-date information.
</P>
<P>
The city has also paid greater attention to teacher training
and provided more than 2,000 teachers last year with modern
education theory and modern technical facilities training.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say that they will make an even greater effort
and will finish installing basic facilities in all primary and
high school within two or three years through the use of social
funds. They also plan to set up information networks on campuses.
</P>
</TEXT>
