<HEADLINE> "Women of China" Celebrates 60th Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Women's Federation (
ACWF) held a ceremony in Beijing today to mark the 60th
anniversary of the founding of the magazine "Women of China".
</P>
<P>
"During the past 60 years, the magazine has carried stories
about outstanding women from all walks of life and has set good
examples for women across the country to learn from," said Peng
Peiyun, vice-chairwoman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress and chairwoman of the ACWF.
</P>
<P>
Peng said that the magazine has opened discussions on the
philosophy of life for women and played an important role in
promoting their awakening and progress.
</P>
<P>
She said that the magazine also played an important role in
spreading knowledge on laws and regulations which can help women
protect their legal rights and get them out of difficulty.
</P>
<P>
"Women of China" was established in Yan'an in northwest China's
Shaanxi Province on June 1, 1939 to encourage women to participate
in the War of Resistance Against Japan (1937-1945).
</P>
<P>
"Thus, 'Women of China' has become an important part of the
media voice of the ACWF," Peng stressed, adding that the magazine
should continue to play an active role in safeguarding the legal
rights of women and children in China and combat the gender
discrimination and other social misconceptions and misdeeds
against them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
