<HEADLINE> Kampala Police Arrest 20 People in Mayoral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- A total of 20 people were arrested
by police for their malpractice during Kampala's mayoral election
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The arrested were trying to disturb the normal proceedings of
the election, Radio Uganda reported Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
However, the report did not say what exactly they did and for
how long the arrested would remain behind the bars for their
misdeeds.
</P>
<P>
There were four official candidates running for the mayorship
vacated by the February sentence of Nasser Sebaggala in the United
States for charges of fraud and lying to customs officers last
year.
</P>
<P>
The race for the key post in the Ugandan capital was, as ever,
characterized by violence of supporters of different candidates.
Police had to shoot to disperse the violent supporters.
</P>
<P>
Some people were reportedly injured during the violence erupted
at the election campaign.
</P>
<P>
With a population of roughly 1.5 million people, Kampala has
about 474, 000 registered voters. The official result of the
election would be announced later Monday, said the radio report.
</P>
</TEXT>
