<HEADLINE> China to Pour 180 Billion Yuan into Highways Construction in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- China plans to invest 180 billion
yuan in the construction of highways this year, which is equal to
that of 1997, according to the Ministry of Communications.
</P>
<P>
Some 110 billion yuan is expected to be poured into 279 major
projects, with a total length of 27,900 kilometers, 15,784
kilometers of which are high-level highways.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country will invest 50 billion yuan in upgrading
a highway network and 20 billion yuan in speeding up the
construction of roads in counties and villages.
</P>
<P>
Last year's actual investment in road construction reached 211.
8 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
