<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigerian Vice President Promises Support for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian government is putting
in place mechanism to ensure that fertilizer and other
agricultural implements reach farmers in time to make this year's
cropping season a success, Vice- President Atiku Abubakar said
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a reception held in his honor in Yola, a city in
Nigeria's eastern state of Taraba, the vice-president said this
year's cropping season has just begun and government is aware of
the need to boost agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
He called on states and local governments to marshal efforts
toward assisting farmers, saying "we are their voice, hopes and
aspirations and ultimately, we will come back to our people to
render account of our stewardship.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president also called on the citizenry to exercise
greater understanding on their part, and support the government to
execute its programs.
</P>
<P>
"We all rose up together and made possible the inception of
this administration, so let us stand together and work for its
success," Alhaji Atiku told thousands of people that attended the
reception organized by the entire states in the North Eastern
region.
</P>
<P>
He said the government will be obliged to take measures that
may seem unpleasant in the short run, but explained that for the
country to move forward in the long run, the bitter pill shall
have to be swallowed.
</P>
<P>
On the state of insecurity, in the North Eastern region in
particular, the vice-president assured that the government would
spare no efforts to ensure the immediate safety and security of
every citizen.
</P>
<P>
"This administration is concerned with the dire state of
insecurity along the north-east axis of our country", he said
amidst cheers.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president is talking about security issue against the
background that about 100 people were killed by suspected
cross-border bandits at the weekend in Taraba state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
