<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Moves to Fight Locust Plague </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- China is intensifying its
fight against a looming severe plague of locusts this summer, with
23 million yuan already raised for the insect-killing drive.
</P>
<P>
The insects have been discovered in great density in nine
Chinese provinces and municipalities so far including Hebei,
Shandong, Henan, Tianjin and Shaanxi, affecting one and a half
times the area in previous normal years, according to the Ministry
of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The prolonged drought and high temperature since last winter
have resulted in the great numbers of locusts and increased swarm
densities.
</P>
<P>
"The locust density has reached as high as more than 3,000
insects per square meter, if the insects grow big enough ten-plus
days later, they could do great harm to crops, and wipe out crops
wherever they pass," said Zhang Shumin, a provincial agriculture
official in northern Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
He added the insect-killing program should be carried out right
now since most of the locusts are discovered in uncultivated land
and beaches and are not blighting crops for the present.
</P>
<P>
With the 23 million yuan of special funds for the insect-
killing program, China has purchased more than 1,200 tons of
pesticides, 100 tons of gasoline and 10,000 pesticide sprayers.
Provinces of Shandong and Hebei even rented seven airplanes for
the program.
</P>
<P>
Those infested areas also stepped up efforts to develop new
biological technologies to eradicate the insect.
</P>
<P>
China's earliest locust disasters date back more than 2,700
years. China has managed to reduce the locust-growing areas to
nearly 20 million mu (about 1.33 million hectares) from 60 million
mu (4 million hectares) in the early 1950s.
</P>
<P>
According to the pledge of the Ministry of Agriculture, China
plans to take ten to 20 years to take the locust plague under
complete control by eradicating the insects in areas between 500,
000 and one million mu annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
