<HEADLINE> Revival in Beijing Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's export volumes for last
month have shown signs of a revival with increases to the United
States, Russia and Japan.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Beijing Customs office show that the city's
total exports and imports in May were 623 million U.S. dollars, 21.
7 percent up, among which 273 were exports, 15.2 percent more, or
11.5 percent more than that of March. And the growth rate for
imports was 27.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The exports to Russia increased by 76.7 percent, and clothing
exports saw a continuous increase.
</P>
<P>
The local government's reforms in the exports market and
product structure have contributed to the growth. And it is very
likely that the city will realize its aim of 2.87 billion U.S.
dollars of exports for the whole year.
</P>
<P>
However, economists warn that in general exports in the first
five months were on the decrease, being 6.4 percent less than that
of the corresponding period last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
