<HEADLINE> Value of Securities Funds Surges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The net value of the securities
investment funds in China's Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchanges
maintained a strong rising momentum last week.
</P>
<P>
The ten securities funds enjoyed a 5 percent to more than 11
percent growth in net value, respectively, during the week,
according to today's China Securities News.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai-listed Yuyang Fund, was the biggest winner, with
its net value reaching 1.428 yuan, up 11.86 percent over the
previous week, topping the ten funds in net value and in the
growth of assets.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attributed the income growth of the funds to the
continuous rally in China's stock markets since May 19 and the
improved expertise of the fund managers. 
</P>
