<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's New Tanker Transport Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The official opening of a Tanker
Transport Committee means that Chinese shipowners will get better
protection from a disorderly market for shipping crude oil and
petroleum products.
</P>
<P>
The committee is under the direct control of the China
Shipowners' Association (CSA) and consists of CSA members, Chen
Zhongbiao, CSA's director, explained at a recent meeting in
Beijing, where he said that the new committee will have a
principle of mutual benefit and cooperation and will set up
reasonable standards for the shipping of crude oil and petroleum
products by water and protect the interests of shipowners.
</P>
<P>
He says that the committee's main task is to carry out state
policies and regulations, to let government departments know about
the needs and desires of members, and to cooperate with
departments in improving relations among ports, cargo owners, and
members.
</P>
<P>
The committee helps meet the market development needs,
according to Yan Mingyi, the general manager of Shanghai's China
Shipping Tanker Co. Ltd. He says that the world's ships carry 1.8
billion tons of crude oil and petroleum products a year, or about
40 percent of the world's total shipping, and that China imports
more than 30 million tons of crude oil each year. Total Chinese
demand for crude oil is expected to reach 190 million tons this
year.
</P>
<P>
Yan emphasizes that the committee is considered to be an
effective way to set more unified transport prices for crude oil
and petroleum products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
