<HEADLINE> Sino-Swedish Cooperation On Sustainable Development Goes Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 21 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Swedish project for China'
s sustained economic development in the 21st century has been
operating smoothly since 1997 for training and consultation on
economic development and environmental protection in various parts
of China, according to Guo Risheng, a vice-director of the project
management.
</P>
<P>
The project includes the city of Shenyang in Liaoning Province,
Nayang in Henan Province, Yantai in Shandong Province, Panzhihua
in Sichuan Province, and 12 other cities. The Central Government
has set up 29 test areas in counties and cities for sustainable
development.
</P>
<P>
The test area in the Shenhe District of Shenyang was set up in
1993 on 17.6 square kilometers of land where the population
density is 33,500 people per sq.km as the first of its kind. It
has finished building model primary schools and a recovery center
for disabled people and 13 other model facilities for improving
people's living quality and for raising people's environmental
protection awareness. 
