<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Province Increasing Forest Coverage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province in south
China has increased its forest coverage in recent years as a
result of extensive afforestation work.
</P>
<P>
It started a forestry policy in 1991 that was centered on "
protecting, reforesting, and developing" and helped afforestation
by stopping illegal logging of forests. The efforts have increased
forest coverage from 4.6 million hectares in 1985 to 9.19 million.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong has also planted 933,000 hectares of cash crops like
tea, bamboo, and fruit trees in addition to more than 11 million
hectares of forest as timber and pine resin production base.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province's forest sector had an output value of
2.36 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The provincial forest industry has got 927 million U.S. dollars
worth of overseas investment, part of which has been used to plant
229,300 hectares of forests.  
</P>
