<HEADLINE> China Sets Up Special Hot-Line for Reporting Crimes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- A special telephone hot-line for
reporting crimes has been set up in procuratorial organs across
the country, officials said today.
</P>
<P>
 The line has the digits "2000" as the last four which will
help people remember it. It is also being fondly tagged as the "
fighter against the corrupt". Anywhere in China, people can dial
the number and be connected to a reporting center in a
procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
 The line has boosted the people's enthusiasm for reporting
offenses and plays a big role in the discovery of graft, bribery
and misconduct in office.
</P>
<P>
 Zhang Qiong, deputy procurator-general of the Supreme People'
s Procuratorate (SPP), said that since it was first introduced
into the SPP last year, the special line has now spread into all
corners of China.
</P>
<P>
 "It is becoming a more and more important tool in fighting
crime for procuratorial organs countrywide," Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
 "At present, cases where the clues have been provided by
ordinary Chinese have accounted for about 80 percent of all those
filed and investigated by procuratorates in China," Zhang added.
</P>
<P>
 In the first four months of this year, procuratorates across
the country received 128,000 reports of offenses, which was 4.94
percent higher than the same period of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
