<HEADLINE> Overseas Loans Helping Chinese Island Province Improve Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Haikou, the capital of China's
island province Hainan has got more overseas loans in recent years
for its diverse environmental protection projects.
</P>
<P>
It is using 5 million U.S. dollars worth of Swedish loans for a
large-scale garbage treatment plant in a mountainous area 30 km.
from the urban area. The project started last April and its first
phase, a 6.7-hectare garbage dump, has been completed.
</P>
<P>
The city government got 300 million yuan (36.6 million U.S.
dollars) from a Hong Kong company to build a power plant with a
daily capacity of 15,000 kilowatts produced by burning 800 tons of
garbage.
</P>
<P>
And a 21.8 million Deutschmark loan from a German bank helped
build an urban sewage treatment plant that went into operation at
the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the city has received 4.9 million U.S. dollars
worth of loans from the Republic of Korea for a water-cleaning
project for the Meishe River. 
</P>
