<HEADLINE> Chinese Officials Discover Quality Problem At State Highway Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Officials are checking on a
serious problem they found at a key state highway project now
under construction.
</P>
<P>
Contractors had been found to be using loose rock instead of
expensive concrete for a major section of the Luoyang-Sanmenxia
Expressway in central China's Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
The highway will link one of China's most famous ancient
capitals with an important reservoir on the Yellow River, and is
expected to cost 4.3 billion yuan (some 500 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Officials say that this has caused great losses and that it
involves a lot of illegal dealing behind the scene.
</P>
<P>
China is conducting a nationwide campaign to examine the
quality of key projects because of some improper construction work.
</P>
</TEXT>
