<HEADLINE> Nigeria Sinks DPR Korea 2-1 in Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PASADENA, California, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria won its
opener in a Group A match as it defeated DPR Korea 2-1 on Sunday
in the women's World Cup tournament, thanks to a brilliant
performance of Mercy Akide.
</P>
<P>
The victory eased the tension the Africans face as they will
meet the United States on Thursday in Chicago.
</P>
<P>
Akide, who scored 10 of Nigeria's 28 goals in the qualifying
rounds, proved to be the cornerstone of Nigeria's striking power
as she opened the mark in the 50th minute, and set up Rita Nwadike
for a winner in the 79th minute.
</P>
<P>
The striker shot pass goalkeeper Yong Sun Kye for a 1-0 lead
before Song Ok Jo levelled on a hard strike from a cross off Jong
Ran Jo.
</P>
<P>
Running down the right flank, Akide passed the ball to Nwadike,
who came at the right time to tap in the cross.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's other three games, Norway beat Russia 2-1,
Australia drew with Ghana 1-1, both at Foxboro, Massachusetts,
while Germany tied Italy 1-1 through a late penalty kick in
Pasadena. 
