<HEADLINE> Chinese Man Sets World Flute Playing Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 21 (Xinhua) -- A man in China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region has set a record on the bamboo flute by playing
it in the widest range.
</P>
<P>
Ding Jian, 39, played two octaves and four scales on his six-
hole flute at a solo concert recently in Urumqi, the regional
capital.
</P>
<P>
Ding says that he has loved music since his childhood and makes
each sound by covering half a hole on the bamboo flute.
</P>
<P>
The flute is an musical instrument with a history of more than
2,000 years and is an indispensable part of Chinese folk music and
a varieties of local operas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
