<HEADLINE> Sino-Russian Border Trade Has Enormous Potential (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 21 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese lawmaker said
here today that there exists enormous potential for Sino-Russian
border economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Zou Jiahua, vice-chairman of the National People's Congress (
NPC) Standing Committee, made the remark at a Sino-Russian seminar
on regional cooperation oriented toward the 21st century, which
opened in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the conviction that through joint efforts made by
local government leaders and entrepreneurs of the two countries,
economic and trade cooperation at the border areas will be further
developed.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day seminar, participants will exchange views on
ways to promote economic and trade cooperation and relations
between sister cities in the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, said in a
letter read at the opening ceremony that friendly exchanges and
mutually beneficial cooperation at the local level between the two
countries enjoy broad prospects.
</P>
<P>
Contacts and cooperation between localities play an active role
in promoting Sino-Russian friendly ties and boosting the
traditional friendship between the people of the two countries, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed the belief that increased cooperation at the local
level will help promote the Sino-Russian strategic and cooperative
partnership featured by equality and mutual trust and geared to
the 21st century, and contribute to promoting cooperation in
political, economic, cultural and other areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
