<HEADLINE> Sino-Russian Border Trade Has Enormous Potential (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yegor Stroyev, chairman of Russia's Federation Council, said in
a letter that the convening of the seminar is a major event in
bilateral relationships, because this year marks the 50th
anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes that Russia-China cooperation in the 21st
century will be featured by political stability, high economic
efficiency, mutual respect and equality between the people of the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, Zou said that border economic
and trade cooperation constitutes an active and important part of
Sino-Russian economic and trade ties. He said that leaders of the
two countries pay close attention to such cooperation, and that
they also signed an agreement on establishing direct economic and
trade links between Chinese provinces and Russian oblasts.
</P>
<P>
So far, China and Russia have opened dozens of border ports.
Statistics showed that the five Chinese provinces and autonomous
regions of Heilongjiang, Jilin, Liaoning, Inner Mongolia and
Xinjiang increased the trade volume with Russia by 30.1 percent on
an annual basis last year.
</P>
<P>
Oleg Korolyov, vice-chairman of Russia's Federation Council,
who is here for the two-day seminar, said that the Russian-Chinese
cooperation potential lies in economic and trade ties between
localities in the two countries. He added that such potential will
play an even bigger role in promoting bilateral economic ties.
</P>
