<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Investment in Thailand to Grow 30 Percent in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 21 (Xinhua) -- German investment in Thailand is
expected to increase by 30 percent this year to 5.7 billion baht
(154 million U.S. dollars), the German-Thai Chamber of Commerce
said in a report, which is available Monday.
</P>
<P>
Direct investment from Germany in Thailand totaled 4.3 billion
baht (116 million dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
To promote further investments in Thailand, the chamber is
organizing a technology symposium in Bangkok in November, which is
expected to attract over 100 companies and will give Thai
manufacturers an opportunity to meet potential partners, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
German companies in pharmaceuticals, metal and auto parts were
showing great interest in Thailand. Some German companies were
shifting their regional offices to Thailand, the report said.
</P>
<P>
German auto parts makers have taken a keen interest in
developing Thailand as a regional hub for manufacturing. BMW is
setting up a plant in Thailand for domestic and international
exports.
</P>
<P>
German direct investment accounted for about one percent of
total foreign investment in 1998. However, it has increased to
about 3 percent and is still rising in 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
