<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Ban Import of Dairy Products From Belgium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government will ban
import of dairy and poultry products from Belgium following
reports of contamination of those items by cancer-causing dioxin,
The Daily Star newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Only a mere formality remains. If the minister signs (the
papers) today, the ban will take effect immediately," Fazlur
Rahman, deputy secretary in the ministry, was quoted as saying on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He said the government had decided to ban only those items from
Belgium because "we have specific information about dioxin
contamination. If needed ban will be imposed on import of such
items from France and the Netherlands also," he said.
</P>
<P>
High-level dioxin was recently detected in Belgian poultry and
eggs, and the contamination also spread to France and the
Netherlands through animal feed, the report said. 
</P>
