</P>
<P>
COLOGNE, Germany -- The Group of Eight (G-8) confined the
international financial aid for Serbia strictly to humanitarian
helps but not any reconstruction funds, said German Chancellor
Gerhard Schroeder on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"We do not think about providing Serbia with reconstruction aid
and helping its integration to Europe", but "we can not punish the
people, we will provide them with humanitarian aid when they are
hungry and cold", Schroeder told a press conference following the
summit. (G8-Reconstruction-Serbia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SINGAPORE -- Singapore's retail sales dipped slightly by 0.5
percent year-on-year in April 1999 after two months of positive
growth while the catering trade inched up by 0.1 percent from
April 1998, the Singapore Department of Statistics said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In April 1999, the country's retail sales totaled 1.79 billion
Singapore dollars (1.05 billion U.S. dollars), growing by 0.1
percent from March, while the catering trade fell by 7.6 percent
from the previous month to a total of 249 million Singapore
dollars (146.17 million U.S. dollars), figures released by the
department show. (Singapore-Retail Sales-Down)
</P>
