<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 12 Others Injured in Brawl in Maluku, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and 12
others injured in a renewed mass brawl at Waab village in
Southeast Maluku district, Indonesia, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Antara News Agency Monday quoted an informed source as saying
that the brawl broke out after hundreds of people riding on at
least 14 sea motor vehicles attacked Waab village as the local
residents were sleeping.
</P>
<P>
The villagers who woke up shortly after the attack tried to
defend themselves and a clash was inevitable.
</P>
<P>
The attackers, armed with sharp weapons and home-made bombs,
took revenge on the villagers following a communal clash in the
area last March, the source said.
</P>
<P>
The dead victim was struck by a home-made bomb shrapnel, and
the 12 injured are now receiving intensive medical treatment at a
hospital.
</P>
<P>
But a number of eyewitnesses said at least seven people among
the attackers were also killed in the clash, and about 40 others
injured.
</P>
</TEXT>
