<HEADLINE> Myanmar FM to Visit Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar Foreign Minister U Win Aung
will pay an official visit to Malaysia soon to further promote
bilateral ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of his Malaysian counterpart Hamid Albar, U
Win Aung will pay the visit, according to an official
announcement here Monday.
</P>
<P>
This will be U Win Aung's another visit to a member country of
the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) after he toured
other ASEAN member countries in February and March this year.
</P>
<P>
In March last year, Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad
officially visited Yangon and an agreement on avoidance of double
taxation and prevention of fiscal evasion with respect to taxes on
income and a memorandum of understanding on mutual exemption of
visas for holders of diplomatic and official passports were
signed.
</P>
<P>
Later in May this year, the two countries also reached a number
of memorandums of understanding on bilateral trade promotion,
investment and cooperation in agriculture and livestock breeding,
and on technical cooperation.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Myanmar-Malaysia bilateral
trade rose from 171.62 million U.S. dollars in 1997 to 280.27
million dollars in 1998 in favor of Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia brought in a capital of 587.17 million dollars in 25
projects at the end of February this year, standing as the fourth
largest foreign investor in Myanmar after Singapore, Britain and
Thailand. 
</P>
