<HEADLINE> Coca Cola Blackmailed for Millions of Marks in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Coca Cola company here got
blackmailed while its problem of product contamination in Belgium
and France had not died, Berlin police said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The German newspaper Die Welt am Sonntag (Sunday World) quoted
police spokesman Hans-Eberhatdt-Schultz as saying that a
blackmailer E-mailed the company four weeks ago, asking it to
remit millions of marks to a certain bank account, or he would
poison its product. However, Schultz denied that this case had
anything to do with the recent Coca Cola product contamination in
France and Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman for Coca Cola in Germany Klaus Hillebrand has refused
to comment on the blackmail report.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the police announced that some 57,000 cans of Coca
Cola had been withdrawn from the German market while authorities
continued to search for any Coca Cola produced in France and
Belgium to ban the sale. 
</P>
