<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fake Money Swindlers Arrested in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Police in Shanxi Province have
arrested three people for selling counterfeit banknotes, and
seized fake money with a total face value 39,000 yuan (about 4,756
US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The arrests were made right on the spot when the three
swindlers were making deals in Xiangning County, according to a
local police source recently.
</P>
<P>
The case is still being investigated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
