<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Korea Wins Archery Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, June 20 (Xinhua) -- South Korea took the men's team
title but lost its women's crown to Germany surprisingly as the
Lucznicza Mermaid Archery Grand Prix concluded here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Yet, South Korea broke both the men's and women's world records
as their men athletes scored 510 points to surpass the previous
mark of 508, while their women compatriots targetted 500 points to
beat the old record of 493 points.
</P>
<P>
En route to their championship, South Korea's men athletes
targetted more than 250 points each round to successively
eliminate Mexico, the Netherlands, Turkey and France from the
quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
France ranked second in the men's team standings, followed by
Italy, Turkey, Ukraine, Germany, the Netherlands and Sweden.
Hosts Poland ranked 15th, followed by Mexico.
</P>
<P>
In the women's event, Germany who scored 245 points,
surprisingly defeated South Korea by five points, while Italy took
the third place after beating Poland 234-232.
</P>
<P>
Ranked fifth to eighth were Ukraine, Turkey, Russia and Belarus.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
