<HEADLINE> Ullrich Skips Tour de France due to Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Jan Ullrich who won the 1997 Tour de
France and finished runner-up last year, will skip the race next
month due to a knee injury.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very sorry, but I won't be racing in the Tour de France
this year," the German said on Sunday in a television interview
from a clinic where he is having treatment.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich was forced out of the Tour of Switzerland with a sore
right knee last Wednesday. He first received the injury in a crash
during the Tour of Germany on May 30.
</P>
<P>
After dropping out of the Swiss race, Ullrich's chances of
contesting the Tour de France were considered slim. He had
originally planned to wait until Monday before making a final
decision.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich said he did not know when he would race again. 
</P>
</TEXT>
