<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany, Russia Win European Cup Athletics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Germany won the men's event in the
European Cup for the first time since 1996 with surprises, while
Russia took away the women's event as expected here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Germany, a European Cup winner from 1994 and 1996, concluded
the two-day competitions with 122 points, beating Italy to a
distant second with 98.5, and defending champion Britain to third
with 97.
</P>
<P>
Among German winners Sunday were Raymond Hecht, who clinched
the javelin with a throw of 86.05 meters, and Jurgen Schult who
won the discus by more than two meters with a throw of 65.68
meters.
</P>
<P>
One of the best races of the day saw Salvatore Vincenti of
Italy win the 3,000 meters in seven minutes 59.12 seconds, just
ahead of Russia's Vyacheslav Shabunin, with 7:59.47 and Frenchman
Driss Maazouzi with 7:59.52.
</P>
<P>
Russia retained its crown in the women's competition as they
began the day with a nine-point lead over Romania, and extended it
during the day, ending with 127 points, 28 clear of the Romanians.
</P>
<P>
Yelena Gulyayeva led the way for Russia, leaping 1.99 meters to
win the high jump. 
</P>
</TEXT>
