<HEADLINE> High Tech, Internet Make Billionaires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 20 (Xinhua) -- Microsoft chief Bill Gates
continued to be listed by Forbes magazine as the world's richest
with net worth of 90 billion U.S. dollars in 1998.
</P>
<P>
For three years running Gates has topped the list of
billionaires, with net up from 36.4 billion dollars in 1996, 51
billion dollars in 1997. His wealth is to surpass 100 billion
dollars coming April, said Forbes which tracks billionaires.
</P>
<P>
According to the July issue of the magazine, high-tech stocks
and the Internet industry are creating new billionaires around the
globe.
</P>
<P>
Among the top ten billionaires in the world, seven have
businesses linked to telecommunications and computers.
</P>
<P>
Among the top seven, three are from Microsoft, with co-founder
Paul Allen worth 30 billion dollars, president Steven Ballmer 19.5
billion dollars in addition to Gates. One of the seven is from
Dell Computer Corp, who is Michael Dell worth of 16.5 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Masayoshi Son, 41, has made his 6.4 billion dollar
fortune through software sales.
</P>
<P>
Forbes says the wealth of top 200 working global billionaires
topped one trillion dollars now, more than double the 463 billion
dollars of 10 years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
